## Exercise 01 ‚Äî Brand Journey Framework

### Desired Outcome

Build a community around E.I. Werner as a fantasy writer and creator that makes the writing career financially sustainable and less lonely. The room full of people who choose to care about the things you've been doing alone for 18 years. Motivate people to full send on their own dreams through the undimmed passion of an 18-year grind with almost nothing to show for it ‚Äî and give fantasy lovers a front-row seat to how the work actually gets made, with real opportunities to engage and contribute along the way. So that when the books are ready, the audience is already there and already cares.

### Reputation Requirement

E.I. Werner is a writer. Writes every day.

### Required Actions

- Three scheduled writing streams per week (the backbone ‚Äî proves "writer who writes every day")
- One scheduled gaming stream per week (community building, personality, connection)
- Casual gaming streams whenever the energy is there
- Monthly public update videos (the rooting interest recruitment tool ‚Äî not gated)
- Share worldbuilding, lore, creation myths, and craft openly. Keep the actual narrative of Only Us protected until it's ready.

### Learning Gaps

- Social media strategy and execution (knowledge gap ‚Äî learnable)
- Comfort on camera (experiential gap ‚Äî requires reps, not study. Confidence is there, warmup period expected)

